{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I just did something I've never done before."},{"time":3000,"text":"I spent a week at sea on a research vessel."},{"time":6000,"text":"Now I'm not a scientist,"},{"time":8000,"text":"but I was accompanying a remarkable scientific team"},{"time":11000,"text":"from the University of South Florida"},{"time":13000,"text":"who have been tracking the travels of BP's oil"},{"time":16000,"text":"in the Gulf of Mexico."},{"time":18000,"text":"This is the boat we were on, by the way."},{"time":21000,"text":"The scientists I was with"},{"time":23000,"text":"were not studying the effect of the oil and dispersants on the big stuff --"},{"time":26000,"text":"the birds, the turtles,"},{"time":28000,"text":"the dolphins, the glamorous stuff."},{"time":30000,"text":"They're looking at the really little stuff"},{"time":33000,"text":"that gets eaten by the slightly less little stuff"},{"time":36000,"text":"that eventually gets eaten by the big stuff."},{"time":39000,"text":"And what they're finding"},{"time":41000,"text":"is that even trace amounts of oil and dispersants"},{"time":44000,"text":"can be highly toxic to phytoplankton,"},{"time":46000,"text":"which is very bad news,"},{"time":48000,"text":"because so much life depends on it."},{"time":51000,"text":"So contrary to what we heard a few months back"},{"time":53000,"text":"about how 75 percent of that oil"},{"time":55000,"text":"sort of magically disappeared"},{"time":57000,"text":"and we didn't have to worry about it,"},{"time":59000,"text":"this disaster is still unfolding."},{"time":62000,"text":"It's still working its way up the food chain."},{"time":65000,"text":"Now this shouldn't come as a surprise to us."},{"time":68000,"text":"Rachel Carson --"},{"time":70000,"text":"the godmother of modern environmentalism --"},{"time":72000,"text":"warned us about this very thing"},{"time":74000,"text":"back in 1962."},{"time":76000,"text":"She pointed out that the \"control men\" --"},{"time":78000,"text":"as she called them --"},{"time":80000,"text":"who carpet-bombed towns and fields"},{"time":82000,"text":"with toxic insecticides like DDT,"},{"time":85000,"text":"were only trying to kill the little stuff, the insects,"},{"time":88000,"text":"not the birds."},{"time":90000,"text":"But they forgot this:"},{"time":92000,"text":"the fact that birds dine on grubs,"},{"time":94000,"text":"that robins eat lots of worms"},{"time":96000,"text":"now saturated with DDT."},{"time":99000,"text":"And so, robin eggs failed to hatch,"},{"time":102000,"text":"songbirds died en masse,"},{"time":104000,"text":"towns fell silent."},{"time":106000,"text":"Thus the title \"Silent Spring.\""},{"time":110000,"text":"I've been trying to pinpoint"},{"time":112000,"text":"what keeps drawing me back to the Gulf of Mexico,"},{"time":114000,"text":"because I'm Canadian,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and I can draw no ancestral ties."},{"time":118000,"text":"And I think what it is"},{"time":120000,"text":"is I don't think we have fully come to terms"},{"time":123000,"text":"with the meaning of this disaster,"},{"time":126000,"text":"with what it meant to witness a hole"},{"time":129000,"text":"ripped in our world,"},{"time":131000,"text":"with what it meant to watch the contents of the Earth"},{"time":134000,"text":"gush forth on live TV,"},{"time":136000,"text":"24 hours a day,"},{"time":138000,"text":"for months."},{"time":140000,"text":"After telling ourselves for so long"},{"time":143000,"text":"that our tools and technology can control nature,"},{"time":146000,"text":"suddenly we were face-to-face"},{"time":148000,"text":"with our weakness,"},{"time":150000,"text":"with our lack of control,"},{"time":152000,"text":"as the oil burst out"},{"time":154000,"text":"of every attempt to contain it --"},{"time":157000,"text":"\"top hats,\" \"top kills\""},{"time":159000,"text":"and, most memorably, the \"junk shot\" --"},{"time":161000,"text":"the bright idea"},{"time":163000,"text":"of firing old tires and golf balls"},{"time":166000,"text":"down that hole in the world."},{"time":168000,"text":"But even more striking"},{"time":170000,"text":"than the ferocious power emanating from that well"},{"time":173000,"text":"was the recklessness"},{"time":175000,"text":"with which that power was unleashed --"},{"time":177000,"text":"the carelessness, the lack of planning"},{"time":180000,"text":"that characterized the operation"},{"time":182000,"text":"from drilling to clean-up."},{"time":185000,"text":"If there is one thing"},{"time":187000,"text":"BP's watery improv act made clear,"},{"time":190000,"text":"it is that, as a culture,"},{"time":192000,"text":"we have become far too willing to gamble"},{"time":194000,"text":"with things that are precious"},{"time":196000,"text":"and irreplaceable,"},{"time":198000,"text":"and to do so without a back-up plan,"},{"time":201000,"text":"without an exit strategy."},{"time":203000,"text":"And BP was hardly"},{"time":205000,"text":"our first experience of this in recent years."},{"time":207000,"text":"Our leaders barrel into wars,"},{"time":209000,"text":"telling themselves happy stories"},{"time":211000,"text":"about cakewalks and welcome parades."},{"time":214000,"text":"Then, it is years of deadly damage control,"},{"time":217000,"text":"Frankensteins of sieges and surges"},{"time":220000,"text":"and counter-insurgencies,"},{"time":222000,"text":"and once again, no exit strategy."},{"time":225000,"text":"Our financial wizards routinely fall victim"},{"time":228000,"text":"to similar overconfidence,"},{"time":230000,"text":"convincing themselves that the latest bubble"},{"time":232000,"text":"is a new kind of market --"},{"time":234000,"text":"the kind that never goes down."},{"time":236000,"text":"And when it inevitably does,"},{"time":238000,"text":"the best and the brightest"},{"time":240000,"text":"reach for the financial equivalent of the junk shot --"},{"time":242000,"text":"in this case, throwing massive amounts"},{"time":244000,"text":"of much-needed public money"},{"time":246000,"text":"down a very different kind of hole."},{"time":249000,"text":"As with BP, the hole does get plugged,"},{"time":251000,"text":"at least temporarily,"},{"time":253000,"text":"but not before"},{"time":255000,"text":"exacting a tremendous price."},{"time":257000,"text":"We have to figure out"},{"time":259000,"text":"why we keep letting this happen,"},{"time":261000,"text":"because we are in the midst"},{"time":263000,"text":"of what may be our highest-stakes gamble of all --"},{"time":266000,"text":"deciding what to do, or not to do,"},{"time":268000,"text":"about climate change."},{"time":270000,"text":"Now as you know,"},{"time":272000,"text":"a great deal of time is spent,"},{"time":274000,"text":"in this country and around the world,"},{"time":276000,"text":"inside the climate debate,"},{"time":278000,"text":"on the question of, \"What if the IPC scientists"},{"time":281000,"text":"are all wrong?\""},{"time":283000,"text":"Now a far more relevant question --"},{"time":285000,"text":"as MIT physicist Evelyn Fox Keller puts it --"},{"time":288000,"text":"is, \"What if those scientists are right?\""},{"time":293000,"text":"Given the stakes, the climate crisis"},{"time":295000,"text":"clearly calls for us to act"},{"time":297000,"text":"based on the precautionary principle --"},{"time":300000,"text":"the theory that holds"},{"time":302000,"text":"that when human health and the environment"},{"time":304000,"text":"are significantly at risk"},{"time":306000,"text":"and when the potential damage is irreversible,"},{"time":309000,"text":"we cannot afford to wait"},{"time":311000,"text":"for perfect scientific certainty."},{"time":313000,"text":"Better to err on the side of caution."},{"time":316000,"text":"More overt, the burden of proving"},{"time":318000,"text":"that a practice is safe"},{"time":320000,"text":"should not be placed on the public that would be harmed,"},{"time":323000,"text":"but rather on the industry that stands to profit."},{"time":327000,"text":"But climate policy in the wealthy world --"},{"time":329000,"text":"to the extent that such a thing exists --"},{"time":332000,"text":"is not based on precaution,"},{"time":334000,"text":"but rather on cost-benefit analysis --"},{"time":337000,"text":"finding the course of action that economists believe"},{"time":339000,"text":"will have the least impact"},{"time":341000,"text":"on our GDP."},{"time":343000,"text":"So rather than asking, as precaution would demand,"},{"time":346000,"text":"what can we do as quickly as possible"},{"time":348000,"text":"to avoid potential catastrophe,"},{"time":351000,"text":"we ask bizarre questions like this:"},{"time":354000,"text":"\"What is the latest possible moment we can wait"},{"time":357000,"text":"before we begin seriously lowering emissions?"},{"time":360000,"text":"Can we put this off till 2020,"},{"time":362000,"text":"2030, 2050?\""},{"time":365000,"text":"Or we ask,"},{"time":367000,"text":"\"How much hotter can we let the planet get"},{"time":369000,"text":"and still survive?"},{"time":371000,"text":"Can we go with two degrees, three degrees, or --"},{"time":373000,"text":"where we're currently going --"},{"time":375000,"text":"four degrees Celsius?\""},{"time":377000,"text":"And by the way,"},{"time":379000,"text":"the assumption that we can safely control"},{"time":381000,"text":"the Earth's awesomely complex climate system"},{"time":384000,"text":"as if it had a thermostat,"},{"time":386000,"text":"making the planet not too hot, not too cold,"},{"time":389000,"text":"but just right -- sort of Goldilocks style --"},{"time":392000,"text":"this is pure fantasy,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and it's not coming from the climate scientists."},{"time":397000,"text":"It's coming from the economists"},{"time":399000,"text":"imposing their mechanistic thinking"},{"time":401000,"text":"on the science."},{"time":403000,"text":"The fact is that we simply don't know"},{"time":405000,"text":"when the warming that we create"},{"time":407000,"text":"will be utterly overwhelmed"},{"time":409000,"text":"by feedback loops."},{"time":411000,"text":"So once again,"},{"time":413000,"text":"why do we take these crazy risks"},{"time":415000,"text":"with the precious?"},{"time":417000,"text":"A range of explanations"},{"time":419000,"text":"may be popping into your mind by now,"},{"time":421000,"text":"like \"greed.\""},{"time":423000,"text":"This is a popular explanation, and there's lots of truth to it,"},{"time":426000,"text":"because taking big risks, as we all know,"},{"time":429000,"text":"pays a lot of money."},{"time":431000,"text":"Another explanation that you often hear for recklessness"},{"time":433000,"text":"is hubris."},{"time":435000,"text":"And greed and hubris"},{"time":437000,"text":"are intimately intertwined"},{"time":439000,"text":"when it comes to recklessness."},{"time":441000,"text":"For instance, if you happen to be a 35-year-old banker"},{"time":444000,"text":"taking home 100 times more"},{"time":446000,"text":"than a brain surgeon,"},{"time":448000,"text":"then you need a narrative,"},{"time":450000,"text":"you need a story"},{"time":452000,"text":"that makes that disparity okay."},{"time":454000,"text":"And you actually don't have a lot of options."},{"time":457000,"text":"You're either an incredibly good scammer,"},{"time":460000,"text":"and you're getting away with it -- you gamed the system --"},{"time":462000,"text":"or you're some kind of boy genius,"},{"time":464000,"text":"the likes of which the world has never seen."},{"time":467000,"text":"Now both of these options -- the boy genius and the scammer --"},{"time":470000,"text":"are going to make you vastly overconfident"},{"time":472000,"text":"and therefore more prone"},{"time":474000,"text":"to taking even bigger risks in the future."},{"time":478000,"text":"By the way, Tony Hayward, the former CEO of BP,"},{"time":481000,"text":"had a plaque on his desk"},{"time":483000,"text":"inscribed with this inspirational slogan:"},{"time":485000,"text":"\"What would you attempt to do"},{"time":487000,"text":"if you knew you could not fail?\""},{"time":490000,"text":"Now this is actually a popular plaque,"},{"time":493000,"text":"and this is a crowd of overachievers,"},{"time":495000,"text":"so I'm betting that some of you have this plaque."},{"time":498000,"text":"Don't feel ashamed."},{"time":500000,"text":"Putting fear of failure out of your mind"},{"time":502000,"text":"can be a very good thing"},{"time":504000,"text":"if you're training for a triathlon"},{"time":506000,"text":"or preparing to give a TEDTalk,"},{"time":509000,"text":"but personally, I think people with the power"},{"time":511000,"text":"to detonate our economy and ravage our ecology"},{"time":514000,"text":"would do better having"},{"time":516000,"text":"a picture of Icarus hanging from the wall,"},{"time":518000,"text":"because -- maybe not that one in particular --"},{"time":521000,"text":"but I want them thinking about the possibility of failure"},{"time":524000,"text":"all of the time."},{"time":526000,"text":"So we have greed,"},{"time":528000,"text":"we've got overconfidence/hubris,"},{"time":530000,"text":"but since we're here at TEDWomen,"},{"time":532000,"text":"let's consider one other factor"},{"time":534000,"text":"that could be contributing in some small way"},{"time":536000,"text":"to societal recklessness."},{"time":540000,"text":"Now I'm not going to belabor this point,"},{"time":542000,"text":"but studies do show that, as investors,"},{"time":544000,"text":"women are much less prone"},{"time":546000,"text":"to taking reckless risks than men,"},{"time":549000,"text":"precisely because, as we've already heard,"},{"time":551000,"text":"women tend not to suffer from overconfidence"},{"time":554000,"text":"in the same way that men do."},{"time":556000,"text":"So it turns out"},{"time":558000,"text":"that being paid less and praised less"},{"time":560000,"text":"has its upsides --"},{"time":562000,"text":"for society at least."},{"time":564000,"text":"The flipside of this"},{"time":566000,"text":"is that constantly being told"},{"time":568000,"text":"that you are gifted, chosen"},{"time":570000,"text":"and born to rule"},{"time":572000,"text":"has distinct societal downsides."},{"time":575000,"text":"And this problem -- call it the \"perils of privilege\" --"},{"time":578000,"text":"brings us closer, I think,"},{"time":580000,"text":"to the root of our collective recklessness."},{"time":583000,"text":"Because none of us -- at least in the global North --"},{"time":585000,"text":"neither men nor women,"},{"time":587000,"text":"are fully exempt from this message."},{"time":590000,"text":"Here's what I'm talking about."},{"time":592000,"text":"Whether we actively believe them"},{"time":594000,"text":"or consciously reject them,"},{"time":596000,"text":"our culture remains in the grips"},{"time":598000,"text":"of certain archetypal stories"},{"time":600000,"text":"about our supremacy"},{"time":602000,"text":"over others and over nature --"},{"time":604000,"text":"the narrative of the newly discovered frontier"},{"time":607000,"text":"and the conquering pioneer,"},{"time":609000,"text":"the narrative of manifest destiny,"},{"time":611000,"text":"the narrative of apocalypse and salvation."},{"time":613000,"text":"And just when you think these stories are fading into history,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and that we've gotten over them,"},{"time":617000,"text":"they pop up in the strangest places."},{"time":620000,"text":"For instance, I stumbled across this advertisement"},{"time":622000,"text":"outside the women's washroom"},{"time":624000,"text":"in the Kansas City airport."},{"time":626000,"text":"It's for Motorola's new Rugged cell phone,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and yes, it really does say,"},{"time":630000,"text":"\"Slap Mother Nature in the face.\""},{"time":632000,"text":"And I'm not just showing it to pick on Motorola --"},{"time":634000,"text":"that's just a bonus."},{"time":636000,"text":"I'm showing it because --"},{"time":638000,"text":"they're not a sponsor, are they? --"},{"time":640000,"text":"because, in its own way,"},{"time":642000,"text":"this is a crass version"},{"time":644000,"text":"of our founding story."},{"time":646000,"text":"We slapped Mother Nature around and won,"},{"time":648000,"text":"and we always win,"},{"time":650000,"text":"because dominating nature is our destiny."},{"time":653000,"text":"But this is not the only fairytale we tell ourselves about nature."},{"time":656000,"text":"There's another one, equally important,"},{"time":659000,"text":"about how that very same Mother Nature"},{"time":661000,"text":"is so nurturing and so resilient"},{"time":664000,"text":"that we can never make a dent in her abundance."},{"time":667000,"text":"Let's hear from Tony Hayward again."},{"time":669000,"text":"\"The Gulf of Mexico is a very big ocean."},{"time":672000,"text":"The amount of oil and dispersants that we are putting into it"},{"time":675000,"text":"is tiny in relation to the total water volume.\""},{"time":678000,"text":"In other words, the ocean is big;"},{"time":680000,"text":"she can take it."},{"time":683000,"text":"It is this underlying assumption of limitlessness"},{"time":686000,"text":"that makes it possible"},{"time":688000,"text":"to take the reckless risks that we do."},{"time":691000,"text":"Because this is our real master-narrative:"},{"time":694000,"text":"however much we mess up,"},{"time":696000,"text":"there will always be more --"},{"time":698000,"text":"more water, more land,"},{"time":701000,"text":"more untapped resources."},{"time":703000,"text":"A new bubble will replace the old one."},{"time":705000,"text":"A new technology will come along"},{"time":707000,"text":"to fix the messes we made with the last one."},{"time":710000,"text":"In a way, that is the story"},{"time":712000,"text":"of the settling of the Americas,"},{"time":714000,"text":"the supposedly inexhaustible frontier"},{"time":716000,"text":"to which Europeans escaped."},{"time":719000,"text":"And it's also the story of modern capitalism,"},{"time":722000,"text":"because it was the wealth from this land"},{"time":724000,"text":"that gave birth to our economic system,"},{"time":727000,"text":"one that cannot survive without perpetual growth"},{"time":730000,"text":"and an unending supply"},{"time":732000,"text":"of new frontiers."},{"time":734000,"text":"Now the problem is"},{"time":736000,"text":"that the story was always a lie."},{"time":738000,"text":"The Earth always did have limits."},{"time":740000,"text":"They were just beyond our sights."},{"time":742000,"text":"And now we are hitting those limits"},{"time":744000,"text":"on multiple fronts."},{"time":747000,"text":"I believe that we know this,"},{"time":749000,"text":"yet we find ourselves trapped in a kind of narrative loop."},{"time":752000,"text":"Not only do we continue to tell and retell"},{"time":755000,"text":"the same tired stories,"},{"time":757000,"text":"but we are now doing so"},{"time":759000,"text":"with a frenzy and a fury"},{"time":761000,"text":"that, frankly, verges on camp."},{"time":764000,"text":"How else to explain the cultural space"},{"time":767000,"text":"occupied by Sarah Palin?"},{"time":769000,"text":"Now on the one hand,"},{"time":771000,"text":"exhorting us to \"drill, baby, drill,\""},{"time":773000,"text":"because God put those resources into the ground"},{"time":776000,"text":"in order for us to exploit them,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and on the other, glorying in the wilderness"},{"time":782000,"text":"of Alaska's untouched beauty"},{"time":784000,"text":"on her hit reality TV show."},{"time":787000,"text":"The twin message is as comforting as it is mad."},{"time":790000,"text":"Ignore those creeping fears"},{"time":792000,"text":"that we have finally hit the wall."},{"time":794000,"text":"There are still no limits."},{"time":796000,"text":"There will always be another frontier."},{"time":799000,"text":"So stop worrying and keep shopping."},{"time":802000,"text":"Now, would that this were just about"},{"time":804000,"text":"Sarah Palin and her reality TV show."},{"time":806000,"text":"In environmental circles,"},{"time":808000,"text":"we often hear that, rather than shifting to renewables,"},{"time":811000,"text":"we are continuing with business as usual."},{"time":814000,"text":"This assessment, unfortunately,"},{"time":816000,"text":"is far too optimistic."},{"time":818000,"text":"The truth is that we have already exhausted"},{"time":821000,"text":"so much of the easily accessible fossil fuels"},{"time":824000,"text":"that we have already entered"},{"time":826000,"text":"a far riskier business era,"},{"time":829000,"text":"the era of extreme energy."},{"time":831000,"text":"So that means drilling for oil in the deepest water,"},{"time":834000,"text":"including the icy Arctic seas,"},{"time":836000,"text":"where a clean-up may simply be impossible."},{"time":839000,"text":"It means large-scale hydraulic fracking for gas"},{"time":842000,"text":"and massive strip-mining operations for coal,"},{"time":844000,"text":"the likes of which we haven't yet seen."},{"time":847000,"text":"And most controversially, it means the tar sands."},{"time":850000,"text":"I'm always surprised by how little"},{"time":852000,"text":"people outside of Canada"},{"time":854000,"text":"know about the Alberta Tar Sands,"},{"time":856000,"text":"which this year are projected to become"},{"time":858000,"text":"the number one source of imported oil"},{"time":861000,"text":"to the United States."},{"time":863000,"text":"It's worth taking a moment to understand this practice,"},{"time":866000,"text":"because I believe it speaks to recklessness"},{"time":868000,"text":"and the path we're on"},{"time":870000,"text":"like little else."},{"time":872000,"text":"So this is where the tar sands live,"},{"time":875000,"text":"under one of the last magnificent"},{"time":877000,"text":"Boreal forests."},{"time":879000,"text":"The oil is not liquid."},{"time":881000,"text":"You can't just drill a hole and pump it out."},{"time":883000,"text":"Tar sand's oil is solid,"},{"time":885000,"text":"mixed in with the soil."},{"time":887000,"text":"So to get at it,"},{"time":889000,"text":"you first have to get rid of the trees."},{"time":892000,"text":"Then, you rip off the topsoil"},{"time":894000,"text":"and get at that oily sand."},{"time":897000,"text":"The process requires a huge amount of water,"},{"time":900000,"text":"which is then pumped into massive toxic tailing ponds."},{"time":904000,"text":"That's very bad news for local indigenous people"},{"time":907000,"text":"living downstream"},{"time":909000,"text":"who are reporting alarmingly high cancer rates."},{"time":912000,"text":"Now looking at these images,"},{"time":914000,"text":"it's difficult to grasp the scale of this operation,"},{"time":917000,"text":"which can already be seen from space"},{"time":920000,"text":"and could grow to an area the size of England."},{"time":923000,"text":"I find it helps actually"},{"time":925000,"text":"to look at the dump trucks that move the earth,"},{"time":927000,"text":"the largest ever built."},{"time":929000,"text":"That's a person down there by the wheel."},{"time":931000,"text":"My point is that"},{"time":933000,"text":"this is not oil drilling."},{"time":935000,"text":"It's not even mining."},{"time":937000,"text":"It is terrestrial skinning."},{"time":939000,"text":"Vast, vivid landscapes"},{"time":941000,"text":"are being gutted,"},{"time":943000,"text":"left monochromatic gray."},{"time":945000,"text":"Now I should confess that as [far as] I'm concerned"},{"time":948000,"text":"this would be an abomination"},{"time":950000,"text":"if it emitted not one particle of carbon."},{"time":952000,"text":"But the truth is that, on average,"},{"time":955000,"text":"turning that gunk into crude oil"},{"time":958000,"text":"produces about three times more greenhouse gas pollution"},{"time":961000,"text":"than it does to produce conventional oil"},{"time":963000,"text":"in Canada."},{"time":965000,"text":"How else to describe this,"},{"time":967000,"text":"but as a form of mass insanity?"},{"time":970000,"text":"Just when we know we need to be learning"},{"time":973000,"text":"to live on the surface of our planet,"},{"time":975000,"text":"off the power of sun, wind and waves,"},{"time":978000,"text":"we are frantically digging"},{"time":980000,"text":"to get at the dirtiest,"},{"time":982000,"text":"highest-emitting stuff imaginable."},{"time":985000,"text":"This is where our story of endless growth"},{"time":987000,"text":"has taken us,"},{"time":989000,"text":"to this black hole at the center of my country --"},{"time":992000,"text":"a place of such planetary pain"},{"time":994000,"text":"that, like the BP gusher,"},{"time":996000,"text":"one can only stand to look at it for so long."},{"time":1000000,"text":"As Jared Diamond and others have shown us,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"this is how civilizations commit suicide,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"by slamming their foot on the accelerator"},{"time":1009000,"text":"at the exact moment"},{"time":1011000,"text":"when they should be putting on the brakes."},{"time":1013000,"text":"The problem is that our master-narrative"},{"time":1016000,"text":"has an answer for that too."},{"time":1018000,"text":"At the very last minute, we are going to get saved"},{"time":1021000,"text":"just like in every Hollywood movie,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"just like in the Rapture."},{"time":1026000,"text":"But, of course, our secular religion is technology."},{"time":1029000,"text":"Now, you may have noticed"},{"time":1032000,"text":"more and more headlines like these."},{"time":1034000,"text":"The idea behind this form of \"geoengineering\" as it's called,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"is that, as the planet heats up,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"we may be able to shoot sulfates and aluminum particles"},{"time":1042000,"text":"into the stratosphere"},{"time":1044000,"text":"to reflect some of the sun's rays"},{"time":1046000,"text":"back to space,"},{"time":1048000,"text":"thereby cooling the planet."},{"time":1051000,"text":"The wackiest plan -- and I'm not making this up --"},{"time":1053000,"text":"would put what is essentially a garden hose"},{"time":1056000,"text":"18-and-a-half miles high into the sky,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"suspended by balloons,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"to spew sulfur dioxide."},{"time":1063000,"text":"So, solving the problem of pollution with more pollution."},{"time":1066000,"text":"Think of it as the ultimate junk shot."},{"time":1070000,"text":"The serious scientists involved in this research"},{"time":1072000,"text":"all stress that these techniques"},{"time":1074000,"text":"are entirely untested."},{"time":1076000,"text":"They don't know if they'll work,"},{"time":1078000,"text":"and they have no idea"},{"time":1080000,"text":"what kind of terrifying side effects they could unleash."},{"time":1083000,"text":"Nevertheless, the mere mention of geoengineering"},{"time":1086000,"text":"is being greeted in some circles,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"particularly media circles,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"with a relief tinged with euphoria."},{"time":1092000,"text":"An escape hatch has been reached."},{"time":1094000,"text":"A new frontier has been found."},{"time":1096000,"text":"Most importantly,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"we don't have to change our lifestyles after all."},{"time":1100000,"text":"You see, for some people,"},{"time":1102000,"text":"their savior is a guy in a flowing robe."},{"time":1104000,"text":"For other people, it's a guy with a garden hose."},{"time":1108000,"text":"We badly need some new stories."},{"time":1111000,"text":"We need stories that have different kinds of heroes"},{"time":1114000,"text":"willing to take different kinds of risks --"},{"time":1117000,"text":"risks that confront recklessness head on,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"that put the precautionary principle into practice,"},{"time":1122000,"text":"even if that means through direct action --"},{"time":1125000,"text":"like hundreds of young people willing to get arrested,"},{"time":1127000,"text":"blocking dirty power plants"},{"time":1129000,"text":"or fighting mountaintop-removal coal mining."},{"time":1132000,"text":"We need stories"},{"time":1134000,"text":"that replace that linear narrative of endless growth"},{"time":1137000,"text":"with circular narratives"},{"time":1139000,"text":"that remind us"},{"time":1141000,"text":"that what goes around comes around."},{"time":1143000,"text":"That this is our only home."},{"time":1145000,"text":"There is no escape hatch."},{"time":1147000,"text":"Call it karma, call it physics,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"action and reaction, call it precaution --"},{"time":1153000,"text":"the principle that reminds us"},{"time":1155000,"text":"that life is too precious to be risked"},{"time":1157000,"text":"for any profit."},{"time":1159000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1161000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}